snippet.textDisplay: Tetris came out in 1984. Gorbachev wouldn't become General Secretary for another year. NATO and WarPact were both following hardline policies against the other, and less than a year ago, Able Archer brought the world to the very edge of catastrophe. 1987 was when Gorbachev started his Perestroika reforms, which is what would ultimately weaken the Soviet Union beyond its breaking point. If Gorbachev hadn't been elected, it would have remained under control of the hardline members of the party, no changes would have been made, the satellite states wouldn't have successfully split away, and the USSR would have most likely persisted a significant while longer, assuming we didn't all die in nuclear fire before that, which would be the more likely outcome.
